OL,3,CGovernment asks body to consult on
OL,4,Caxing 'discriminatory' minimum wage
OL,5,Cage bands
OL,7,FThe Government has said it is pushing
OL,8,Fforward with plans to look at removing
OL,9,F"discriminatory" age bands for the
OL,10,Fnational minimum wage as it extended
OL,11,Fthe remit of the Low Pay Commission
OL,12,F(LPC).
OL,14,FIt said the advisory body will consult
OL,15,Fwith employers, trade unions and
OL,16,Fworkers on narrowing the gap between
OL,17,Fthe minimum wage rate for 18 to 20-
OL,18,Fyear-olds, and the so-called national
OL,19,Fliving wage ` the UK minimum wage for
OL,20,Fworkers 21 years and older.
